cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with speech recognition and language modeling. It could also belong to cs.SD (Sound) as it deals with speech signals. Additionally, it involves the use of neural networks, which makes it relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the use of attention modeling to improve the performance of the system makes it relevant to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
